cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.CC, cs.DS, cs.PL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the logic of Boolean connectives and axiomatization of Classical Propositional Logic. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a likely category as logic is a fundamental component of AI and the paper may have implications for the development of logical systems in AI. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is a possible category as the paper may involve complexity analysis of the merging of fragments of logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possible category as the paper may involve the development of algorithms for merging fragments of logic. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper may have implications for the design and implementation of programming languages that use logic.
